        <div class="two-col-layout">
            <div class="left-column">
                <section class="hero hero-compact">
                    <figure class="hero-media">
                        <img src="/web/20260324104212im_/http://coffeepowered.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/img/stanton.png" alt="Paul Stanton headshot">
                    </figure>
                    <div class="hero-content">
                        <h1>Paul Stanton</h1>
                        <p class="intro">I operate at the intersection of AI, platform experience, and organisational leverage. I focus on building confidence, explainability, and sustainable scale without increasing risk or headcount.</p>
                        <div class="hero-cta">
                            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://www.linkedin.com/in/paulstanton/">Follow me on LinkedIn</a>
                            <a class="btn" href="/web/20260324104212/http://coffeepowered.co.uk/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#0e7e6f7b624e6d6168686b6b7e61796b7c6b6a206d61207b65">Email Me</a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="hero-facts" aria-label="Quick profile metrics">
                            <article>
                                <p class="fact-label">Focus</p>
                                <p class="fact-value">AI / Platform / UX</p>
                            </article>
                            <article>
                                <p class="fact-label">Base</p>
                                <p class="fact-value">Leeds, UK</p>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="panel spread" aria-label="About Paul">
                    <h2>About</h2>
                    <div class="writing-spread">
                        <article class="writing-block">
                            <h3>What I Solve</h3>
                            <p>I identify where confidence, explainability, or scale are limiting growth, then design platform-level capabilities that reduce delivery risk while accelerating customer and commercial outcomes.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="writing-block">
                            <h3>How I Work</h3>
                            <p>I work in a founder-mode pattern: conceiving and prototyping end to end, then deliberately transitioning ownership to specialist teams once value is proven and repeatable.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="writing-block">
                            <h3>Design Grounding</h3>
                            <p>My background in user experience and accessibility, shaped in complex public-sector delivery, keeps AI products understandable, inclusive, and safe to operate at scale.</p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="panel spread" aria-label="Selected work" id="work">
                    <h2 id="work-heading">Selected Work</h2>
                    <div class="work-spread">
                        <article class="work-block">
                            <h3>Agent-Ex: Search</h3>
                            <p>Conceived and prototyped rapidly, then transitioned into a core Jadu product through structured evaluation and cross-functional knowledge transfer. Now live with public-sector organisations and expanding through partner channels.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://www.jadu.net/agent-ex" aria-label="Open project link for Agent-Ex: Search"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> jadu.net/agent-ex</a></p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=igmUE5j3tU8" aria-label="Watch the video for Agent-Ex: Search"><i class="fa fa-youtube-play" aria-hidden="true"></i> Watch the video</a></p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="work-block">
                            <h3>Pragmatic Evaluation Framework</h3>
                            <p>Designed a Red / Amber / Green confidence model that turns AI evaluation into a clearer, repeatable go-live process, reducing manual overhead and improving explainability for risk-averse stakeholders.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://aipsweek.digileaders.com/talks/from-black-box-to-green-light-shipping-ai-with-confidence/" aria-label="Watch the talk for Pragmatic Evaluation Framework"><i class="fa fa-youtube-play" aria-hidden="true"></i> Watch the talk</a></p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="work-block">
                            <h3>Jadu Assist (Formerly Jadu Labs)</h3>
                            <p>Built as a safe incubation channel to prototype and validate AI features without disrupting core teams, then transitioned into a named, supported product owned by specialist teams.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://jadu.net/assist" aria-label="Open project link for Jadu Assist"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> jadu.net/assist</a></p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://youtu.be/OZC5PgNojmc" aria-label="Watch the video for Jadu Assist"><i class="fa fa-youtube-play" aria-hidden="true"></i> Watch the video</a></p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="work-block">
                            <h3>Visual Workflow</h3>
                            <p>Designed to reduce cognitive load when managing complex workflows, helping teams design and deliver critical front-line public-sector services faster and with more confidence.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://jadu.net/assist" aria-label="Open project link for Visual Workflow"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> jadu.net/assist</a></p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3en_vZxXAX4&amp;t=308s" aria-label="Watch the talk for Visual Workflow"><i class="fa fa-youtube-play" aria-hidden="true"></i> Watch the talk</a></p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="work-block">
                            <h3>Content Assist</h3>
                            <p>AI-assisted content tooling focused on clarity, consistency, and speed of delivery for service teams producing high-volume public-facing content.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://jadu.net/assist" aria-label="Open project link for Content Assist"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> jadu.net/assist</a></p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cTDQJ9lmNW0&amp;list=PLaSEo9Kcg2FfWzKRUYy9D9nmSbnB8e7t4&amp;index=5&amp;pp=iAQBsAgC" aria-label="Watch the video for Content Assist"><i class="fa fa-youtube-play" aria-hidden="true"></i> Watch the video</a></p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="work-block">
                            <h3>Pulsar</h3>
                            <p>Design system foundations that improve consistency and accessibility across product teams, reducing duplication while supporting predictable delivery at scale.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://jadu.github.io/pulsar/" aria-label="Open project link for Pulsar"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> jadu.github.io/pulsar/</a></p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rmGUTvuBvdw&amp;pp=ygURcGF1bCBzdGFudG9uIGphZHU%3D" aria-label="Watch the talk for Pulsar"><i class="fa fa-youtube-play" aria-hidden="true"></i> Watch the talk</a></p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="panel spread" aria-label="Writing" id="writing">
                    <h2 id="writing-heading">Writing</h2>
                    <div class="writing-spread">
                        <article class="writing-block">
                            <h3>Which accessibility testing tool should you use?</h3>
                            <p>A practical breakdown of tool tradeoffs and workflow for production teams.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://medium.com/pulsar/which-accessibility-testing-tool-should-you-use-e5990e6ef0a" aria-label="Open writing link for Which accessibility testing tool should you use?"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> medium.com/pulsar/which-accessibility-testing-tool-should-you-use-e5990e6ef0a</a></p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="writing-block">
                            <h3>Retiring pieces of a design system</h3>
                            <p>How to safely deprecate components without breaking product delivery.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://medium.com/pulsar/retiring-pieces-of-a-design-system-d5ebb080d755" aria-label="Open writing link for Retiring pieces of a design system"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> medium.com/pulsar/retiring-pieces-of-a-design-system-d5ebb080d755</a></p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="writing-block">
                            <h3>Pulsar - The design system for Jadu</h3>
                            <p>The system thinking behind product consistency at platform scale.</p>
                            <p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260324104212/https://medium.com/pulsar/pulsar-the-design-system-for-jadu-6ce0031fa28a" aria-label="Open writing link for Pulsar - The design system for Jadu"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> medium.com/pulsar/pulsar-the-design-system-for-jadu-6ce0031fa28a</a></p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                </section>

